<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1814-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1814-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Monroe</persName>,
                                    Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Conner</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1814-04-19"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 19,
                                1814</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The papers referred to in your letter
                                of the 7th instant were duly received at this office. The United
                                States being at peace with Spain, no countenance can be given by
                                their Government to the proceedings of the revolutionary party in
                                East Florida, if it is composed of Spanish subjects, and still less
                                can it be given to them if it consists of American citizens, who, so
                                far as their conduct may fall within the scope of existing laws long
                                enacted and well known and understood, will be liable to
                                censure.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>JAMES MONROE.</signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson Conner</hi>, Esq.,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Louisburgh, North Carolina.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>